```python
import pytesseract
from PIL import Image

def extract_information_from_invoice(image_path):
    # Load the image
    img = Image.open(image_path)

    # Use pytesseract to perform OCR on the image
    text = pytesseract.image_to_string(img)

    # Print the extracted text
    print(text)

    # Initialize the dictionary to store extracted information
    invoice_info = {
        "work_order_number": "",
        "total_cost": ""
    }

    # Split the text into lines for easier processing
    lines = text.split('\n')

    # Process each line to extract relevant information
    for line in lines:
        if "Estimate Number:" in line:
            work_order_number = line.split(":")[1].strip()
            invoice_info["work_order_number"] = work_order_number
        elif "Grand Total" in line:
            total_cost = line.split(":")[1].strip()
            invoice_info["total_cost"] = total_cost

    return invoice_info

# Replace 'invoice.jpg' with the path to your invoice image file
image_path = 'invoice.jpg'
extracted_info = extract_information_from_invoice(image_path)
extracted_info
```
